<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Silver Zooms Up in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Silver Prices zoomed up by
100 rupees (2.33 U.S. dollars) per kilogram on the bullion market
Thursday in Mumbai (Bombay), while gold prices remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold and twenty-two-carat gold both were quoted
unaltered at 4,530 rupees (105.35 dollars) and 4,210 rupees (97.91
dollars) per 10 grams respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, ready silver (.999 fineness) ended at 8,260 rupees (
192.09 dollars) per kilogram, showing a rise of 100 rupees (2.33
dollars) over the last close of 8,160 rupees (189.77 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) went up by 110 rupees (2.56 dollars)
to 8,165 rupees (189.88 dollars) per kg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
