<HEADLINE> Hijackers, Taliban Give New Ultimatum to India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Hijackers of an Indian
Airlines plane have given a new ultimatum to India to release 36
Muslim militants till Friday, otherwise they will be forced to
take an extreme step, Pakistan state-run television reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The television, however, did not give the details of the
ultramatum.
</P>
<P>
The hijackers seized the plane last Friday and are now holding
more than 150 passengers and crew hostage on board at the Kandahar
airport in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Afghanistan's Taliban have also asked India to
resolve the crisis till Friday otherwise the hijacked plane will
be forced to leave the Kandahar airport.
</P>
<P>
The plane has been stranded at the airport over the past six
days and an Indian negotiating team have been in talks with the
hijackers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
