<HEADLINE> Over 50 Feared Burnt Alive in Bus Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Some 52 passengers were
feared burnt alive and 24 others seriously injured Thursday when a
bus turned turtle and caught fire in northern Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The bus was badly burnt and most of the bodies of the
passengers were mutilated beyond recognition, according to the
Associated Press of Pakistan (APP).
</P>
<P>
Police have confirmed 48 dead and feared the figure might go up
a little.
</P>
<P>
The speeding bus broke the motorway fence at 15:20 local time (
1020 GMT) near Kallar Kahar in northern Punjab province and rolled
over several times before catching fire, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident remains unconfirmed, though a short
circuit was suspected to have ignited the fire.
</P>
<P>
According to APP, more than 70 passengers were on board,
including women and children when the incident occurred. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
