<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Upbeat over Hijack Negotiations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Afghan Taliban's Foreign
Minister Wakil Ahmed Mutawakil said Thursday he was" optimistic
about negotiations between India with hijackers of an Indian
Airlines plane stranded in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
"The key problems are where will the hijackers be sent, and
where will Kashmiri prisoners in India go if they are released,"
Mutawakil was quoted by news reaching here as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the Taliban-led government had been discussing how to
handle these problems with the United Nations, Indian officials
and western diplomats.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban official, however, ruled out possibility of
political asylum for the hijackers in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The Indian plane was hijacked last Friday and has been grounded
at the Kandahar airport over the past six days with more than 150
passengers and crew on board held as hostage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
