<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Concerned About Military Coup in Cote d'Ivoire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) on
Thursday expressed concern over the military coup in Cote d'Ivoire,
according to a statement released here.
</P>
<P>
In a Finnish presidential statement, the EU voiced its deep
concern over the military coup and the dissolution of political
and legal institutions in Cote d'Ivoire on December 24.
</P>
<P>
The statement urged all parties to restore peacefully and
rapidly a democratic constitutional rule in the country, to
respect human rights and to guarantee security during the
transitional period.
</P>
<P>
The EU would like to express its support for the Organization
of the African Unity Summit on its decision reached last July,
which condemned any military coup and resolved to isolate any
government which came to power by force, the statement added.
</P>
<P>
Finland holds the current six-month rotating presidency of the
EU, which ends tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
