<HEADLINE> HK 100 New District Council Members Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, has
appointed 100 District Council members for a four-year term
staring from January 2000, a government spokesman announced
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
All the 100 appointees have agreed to accept the appointment,
and they are appointed for their enthusiasm and familiarity with
community affairs, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"They are appointed in their personal capacity and having
regard to their experience and ability to serve the community ,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added that the government was still in the
process of approaching a couple of other prospective appointees.
Their names would be announced later when they had indicated
acceptance of appointment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
