<DOCNO> XIE19991231.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Sees Employment Rise in All Service Sectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 30 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong witnessed a big
rise in employment in all service sectors in the third quarter of
this year over a year earlier, according to the figures released
Thursday by the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
On a year-on-year comparison, the growth in employment in
September 1999 was the most significant in the wholesale, retail
and import and export trades, restaurants and hotels sector, with
a total 997,5000 people engaged, the figures showed.
</P>
<P>
However, employment of manual workers at construction sites and
in the manufacturing sector continued on a declining trend, but
smaller than in the earlier periods.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the department, a rebound in the
total number of vacancies was registered in transport, storage and
communications sector, and the wholesale, retail and hotels sector
in September 1999.
</P>
<P>
For all the sectors surveyed taken together, there were around
27,800 vacancies in September, of which 24,800 were in the private
sector and the other 3,000 in the civil service, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the report showed that the average payroll per
person engaged for all the major sectors surveyed taken together
decreased by 1.1 percent in nominal terms in the third quarter
1999 over a year earlier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
