<HEADLINE> Khamenei Calls for Annihilation of Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Iran's paramount leader
Ayatollah Seyed Ali Khamenei again called for the annihilation of
Israel on the occasion of the international Qods (Jerusalem) day
Friday.
</P>
<P>
"There is only one solution to the Middle East problem, namely
the annihilation and destruction of the Zionist (Israeli) state,"
Khamenei said at the Friday prayers on the campus of Tehran
University.
</P>
<P>
"From Islamic, humanitarian, economic, security and political
points of view, today the presence of Israel is a very big threat
against the regional nations and states," he said.
</P>
<P>
In 1980, the late Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah Musavi
Khomeini announced the last Friday of the Islamic holy fasting
month of Ramadan as the International Qods Day, calling for
international support for the Palestinians to "liberate" Jerusalem
from Israeli occupation.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of fasting Iranians from various walks of life
on Friday poured into streets to voice their support for the
Palestinian struggles and condemning any compromise with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the large gathering, Khamenei said that "Israel is
now in possession of nuclear arsenal and continues to produce
weapons, it has not heeded the warnings of the United Nations
either, mainly because of the U.S. support."
</P>
<P>
From economic point of view, Khamenei said, the Zionists want to
create a so-called "new Middle East" with Israel dominating the
region economically.
</P>
<P>
"They aim to gradually dominate the Arab countries in the region
economically and then the oil-rich states in the Persian Gulf," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
After breaking ties with Tel Aviv after the 1979 Islamic
revolution, Tehran has always refused to recognize the Jewish
state, labelling it "the usurper of Islamic lands."
</P>
<P>
Tehran has also opposed the Middle East peace process and any
compromise with Israel, calling for military struggle to root out
Israel.
</P>
<P>
However, the Iranian government has adopted milder policies
towards the peace process by declaring it would not take any action
to undermine the peace process, though Tehran is against it.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei also lashed out at the U.S., certain western countries
and international human rights organizations for turning a blind
eye to "the atrocities committed by the Zionist regime."
</P>
<P>
He urged the Palestinians not to vest any hope in peace talks
with Israel, saying that "peace is only a ploy by the Zionists to
prepare for their future aggressions."
</P>
<P>
He underlined that the Palestinian issue is the main problem of
the Islamic world, noting that the Palestinian refugees must return
to their homeland.
</P>
<P>
Muslims throughout the world had every duty to defend the
Palestinians in whatever possible manner, he said, "part of the
Islamic land is under the occupation of the enemy and we Muslims
are all duty bound to defend the land and return it to its main
owners." 
</P>
</TEXT>
