<HEADLINE> Simitis: Greece Welcomes New Year With Optimism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis said Friday that his country welcomes the new year with
optimism, self-confidence, prestige and strength.
</P>
<P>
Wishing for health, happiness and prosperity to all Greeks in
his New Year message, Simitis said that Greece has become a better
country and offers to its people opportunities for economic
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
The year 2000 will be the year in which Greece will join the
European economic and monetary union (EMU), and Greece will shield
its economy even more effectively and will open more prospects for
development and prosperity, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the need of an intense effort, adding that the
course followed was not easy as it was characterized by many
challenges.
</P>
<P>
Simitis said that Greece kept a steady course based on reason
and it became a factor of stability and peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
He said that the relations with neighboring Turkey were led to
a new road within the framework of the European Union and that the
road of peace and understanding is open and Turkey can seize the
opportunity opened for the interest of both Greece and Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Greek President Costis Stephanopoulos said in a new year
message that he wishes for no more wars, poverty and untreated
diseases. 
</P>
