<HEADLINE> Over 200,000 Refugees Enter Zambia: UNHCR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has 205,300 refugees
within its border, most of whom are fleeing armed conflicts in
neighboring countries, according to statistics released by the
United Nations High Commission for Refugees (UNHCR) Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics, 161,680 refugees were from Angola
while 36, 331 from the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) and
the rest from Burundi, Rwanda and Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Zambia has continued to receive huge numbers of refugees
fleeing fighting Angola and the DRC.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, UNHCR said that the "logistics" needed to set up
refugees transit centers in Kalabo and Mongu in Zambia's Western
Province has already been sent to the two cities and construction
has begun. 
</P>
</TEXT>
