<HEADLINE> Sacred Flame Reaches Millennium Celebration Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The torch of the Sacred Flame
of China reached the China Centenary Altar, the site for a grand
ceremony held here to greet the advent of a new millennium, today.
</P>
<P>
The torch was carried by 22-year-old Beijing University student
Dabenna of the Mongolian ethnic, who was followed by eight Modern
Maidens holding flowers.
</P>
<P>
After passing the 270-meter-long path paved in bronze, Dabenna
placed the torch on the flame-lighting stage.
</P>
<P>
The sacred flame is a symbol of the long civilization of the
Chinese nation which will be passed on generation after generation.
The flame's journey to the altar began at Zhoukoudian, 48
kilometers from the Beijing urban area, where archaeologists
discovered the fossil remains of Peking Man.  
