<HEADLINE> Spectacular Celebrations to Greet New Millennium in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital held a
series of spectacular celebrations today to greet new century and
new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Those involved in a grand ceremony at the China Centenary Altar
showed great joy when the celebrations started. A 50-meter-long
huge dragon, escorted by eight other dragons, were fluttering on a
platform; forty-five young couples were dancing cheerfully; actors
and actresses were providing vivid Beijing opera for audience; and
children were brandishing flowers alongside the altar.
</P>
<P>
The altar, covering an area of 4.5 hectares, was decorated with
red lanterns and colorful lamps. The project was just completed as
the only large symbolic structure to greet the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 10,000 people from a dozen districts and counties of
Beijing sang and danced at a road section from the altar to
Beijing West Railway Station. All of them expressed their wishes
for a more magnificent China and a more bright future.  
