<HEADLINE> Air China Flies Safely for 45 Full Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Air China's last flight of 1999
returned from Tokyo and landed safely at Beijing Capital
International Airport at 9:35 p.m. tonight.
</P>
<P>
With the completion of this flight, the airline established a
perfect safety record, flying safely for 45 consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
Air China, founded in 1955, currently has 3,200 pilots and
crew members and 44 big and medium-sized aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The airline boasts 60 domestic routes and 72 international
routes, and handles safe take-offs and landings at more than 200
airports in over 100 countries.
</P>
<P>
Air China has so far safely flown for more than 4.3 million
hours and handled a transport turnover of over 28 billion ton-km.
</P>
