<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Publishes New Year Message (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the past year, the Chinese people celebrated the 50th
founding anniversary of new China, and the smooth return of Macao
to the motherland, the message recalls.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Chinese people, united as one, in the past year
denounced the U.S.-led NATO bloc for its bombing of the Chinese
embassy in the Federation of Yugoslavia, the message notes, and
repudiated the "two-states" theory peddled by Lee Teng-hui of
Taiwan and the Falun Gong evil cult organization.
</P>
<P>
During the past year, remarkable achievements were attained in
China's reform, opening and economic development in spite of the
fairly complicated domestic and international environment. The
state revenue was on the rise, the livelihood of the Chinese
people continued to improve, stability was maintained in China's
political situation, all ethnic groups were harmonious, and China'
s international standing was upgraded further, the message says.
</P>
<P>
And the coming year of 2000, the last year of the current
century, which serves as a vital link between the past and the
future, is still faced with the arduous task of carrying out
reform and development and stability.
</P>
<P>
The message urges the entire Chinese people to keep in high
spirits, be full of vitality for further enhancing the nation's
economic strength, defense capabilities and national cohesion, so
as to comprehensively advance the cause of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Developing the economy and improving national strength calls
for a united, stable domestic environment as well as a sound
international environment favorable to China's stability and
development, the message adds.
</P>
<P>
Noting that stability is an overall, overwhelming issue, the
message stresses that nothing can be done without the attainment
of stability, and people should value all the more this good
situation and seize the opportunity to do China's things well.
</P>
<P>
Internationally, the message notes, peace and development
remain the themes of our time, and the world's polarization
continues to develop, and major progress has been made in China's
foreign affairs work.
</P>
<P>
Mankind has scored amazing successes in the past two millennia.
The Chinese nation, with one-fifth of the world's population, will
shoulder still greater responsibilities for creating a bright
future for the world, the message says.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a leading Chinese ideological journal, "Seeking
Truth", has also published a New Year's editorial titled "Striding
Proudly Ahead into the New Century."  
</P>
</TEXT>
