<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Australians Greet New Millennium in  Spectacular Style </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Australians greeted 2000 in
spectacular style with nearly a million people cramming Sydney's
harbor-side for the biggest new year's bash in the nation's
history.
</P>
<P>
On the stroke of the new millennium in Sydney, the crowd looked
skyward as a breathtaking pyrotechnic mass burst high into the
night along the city's iconic harbor bridge.
</P>
<P>
Fireworks exploded up to 1,000 meters and cascaded from the
bridge.
</P>
<P>
Multi-coloured star-bursts, showers of fire and waterfalls of
light accompanied a soundtrack from the last thousand years as
Sydney said goodbye at once to an old year, decade, century and
millennium.
</P>
<P>
Innumerable camera flashes answered back from an estimated 900,
000 revellers who staked out prime positions up to 48 hours
earlier.
</P>
<P>
Partying at the harbor, British tourist Danny Anderson, 26,
spoke for many.
</P>
<P>
"It's been absolutely fantastic," he said. "I can't deny that
Sydney is the best place on earth to be tonight."
</P>
<P>
Billed as the largest such display ever seen in Australia, the
6-million-Australian dollar (3.96 million U.S. dollars)
spectacular burned through 20 tonnes of fireworks in just under 30
minutes.
</P>
<P>
At its close, the single word "Eternity" lit up on the eastern
side of the harbor bridge.
</P>
<P>
The harbor itself was packed with an estimated 6,000 spectator
craft ranging from luxury yachts and cruisers to dingies and
canoes.
</P>
<P>
A procession of giant illuminated lanterns in the shape of sea
creatures moved up and down the waterway before gathering in front
of the Opera House.
</P>
<P>
The weather, though blustery, remained dry for the celebrations.
</P>
<P>
At the close of the fireworks, the bells of St Marys and St
Andrew's cathedrals tolled for the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Emergency services reported no major incidents to midnight:
police said there had been no arrests and the ambulance service
reported 350 minor incidents.
</P>
<P>
In Canberra, the celebrations at the bank of the Lake Burley
Griffin were highlighted by fireworks show mid-night when
revellers waved and sang songs.
</P>
<P>
In Melbourne, thousands of revellers gathered to watch an array
of entertainers ahead of the midnight crackers.
</P>
<P>
However, the river parade did not quite live up to expectations.
</P>
<P>
"I think it's good that people are having a go. It may not be
the best procession ever but people are having a go and enjoying
themselves. It's fantastic," Steve Bracks, premier of the Victoria
state, said.
</P>
<P>
Bracks put the numbers of party-goers on the river precinct at
500,000 although Victoria police were not quite as enthusiastic,
saying there were about 30,000 at 10 p.m. and growing.
</P>
<P>
In Brisbane, police and ambulance officers were amazed at how
quiet the evening had been, with no incidents reported state-wide.
</P>
<P>
Brisbane police were even asking whether new year's eve had
been postponed.
</P>
<P>
Crowds in the city were described as not much bigger than a
normal Friday night.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 50,000 people flocked to Brisbane's South Bank.
</P>
<P>
In Perth, new year's celebrations were muted after a severe
bush fire ravished homes in the Hills district of the city.
</P>
<P>
Several houses were destroyed and 60 residents evacuated before
the flames were brought under control.  
</P>
</TEXT>
