<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Text of Yeltsin's Resignation Address </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
announced his resignation Friday in a televised address to the
nation. He handed his powers to Prime Minister Vladimir Putin, who
is serving as the acting president.
</P>
<P>
The following is the abridged text of Yeltsin's address:
</P>
<P>
Dear friends,
</P>
<P>
I address my New Year greeting to you for the last time today.
I address you for the last time as the Russian President today.
</P>
<P>
I have made a decision.
</P>
<P>
I have been long and hard thinking about this decision. Today,
on the last day of the outgoing year, I resign.
</P>
<P>
I am leaving before my term in office is over. I realize that I
must do this. Russia should enter the new millennium with new
politicians, new people -- clever, energetic and strong, while we,
who have been in power for many years, should rather go.
</P>
<P>
When I saw how much hope and faith was pinned on a new
generation of politicians in the elections to the State Duma, I
realized that I have fulfilled the main task of my life. Russia
will never go back to the past. Russia will always move forward
now.
</P>
<P>
I should not be in the way of the natural course of history.
What's the point of holding on to power when the country has a
strong man worthy to be president and on whom practically every
citizen of Russia pins his hopes for the future now. Why should I
be in his way? Why should I wait for another six months? It is not
for me. It is not my character.
</P>
<P>
Today, which is a very important day for me, I want to
apologize.
</P>
<P>
I apologize because our dreams have not come true; I apologize
because I have not lived up to the expectations of those who
believed that by a single push, by a single leap....
</P>
<P>
However, things have not worked by a single push. I seemed to
be naive while problems proved to be much more difficult. We had
been going forward through mistakes and failures. Many people have
experienced shock during this time.
</P>
<P>
I have never said this before, but I want to say now that the
pain experienced by each of you turned into pain in my own heart.
I spent sleepless nights tortured by thoughts of what should be
done to help people live better.
</P>
<P>
I am leaving. I have done all I could. I am leaving not for
health reasons, but because of the knot of problems. A new
generation is coming to replace me. The generation of those who
can do much more and do it better.
</P>
<P>
Saying good-bye, I want to wish happiness to everyone.
</P>
<P>
Happy New Year and welcome to the next century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991231.0064 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
