<HEADLINE> China Coal Export Exceeds 31 Million Tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The China Coal Import and
Export Group Corporation is reported to have exported 31 million
tons of coal through December 30, a record of 1.75 million tons
more than last year.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the international coal price has steadily
dropped, discouraging most export coal manufacturers. Playing a
major role in China's coal export, the Import and Export Group
Corporation has taken measures to cut commission fees to 1.5 per
cent and tried to improve general service, thus helping the
producers getting an extra 20 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, 93 percent of the coal exports are
produced in State-owned enterprises (SOE). Exporting has proved
effective in lifting coal SOEs out of difficulty. 
</P>
