<HEADLINE> Ice Festival Opens in Harbin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The 16th ice festival in the
northern Chinese city of Harbin opened here tonight.
</P>
<P>
This year's festival boasts many historic firsts, among them
the Ice and Snow World, which occupies 200,000 square meters and
is more than three times bigger than the previous one.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of ice and snow used at the festival reached
190,000 cubic meters, six times more than the average of the past
festivals.
</P>
<P>
This year also saw the debut of the highest ice building ever
seen at the festival, a 36.9-meter-high bell tower built
specially for the occasion and for the millennium celebrations.
</P>
<P>
Over 500 activities will be held, including ice weddings, snow
football matches and winter swimming.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, activities related to trade and economic
cooperation have been organized. 
