<HEADLINE> New Peace Symbol Unveiled in Phnom Penh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, December 31 (Xinhua) -- A new symbol of peace: a
more than 3-ton gun with a knot in the barrel was unveiled Friday
in the park near the Cambodian-Japanese Friendship Bridge.
</P>
<P>
Sar Kheng, deputy prime minister and minister of interior, and
the city Governor Chea Sophara presided over the ceremony. Also at
present were some diplomats and the officials from non-government
organizations. More than 2,000 people also took part in the
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"This event is of great historical significance of the capital
of Phnom Penh, the political, economic and cultural seat of the
kingdom of Cambodia, and it can mark the end of the armed violence
and the end of the old year 1999, of the old century, the 20th,
and of the old millennium as well," Sar Kheng said.
</P>
<P>
"The twisted barrel gun will serve as a token of the Royal
government's new thinking and Cambodians' aspiration: we no longer
need weapons and make war. We need peace and safety only," added
Sar Kheng.
</P>
<P>
The "twisted barrel gun" was made of metal pieces of more than
4,000 confiscated weapons destroyed on May 5, 1999, the day
marking the destruction of weapons at the national stadium.
</P>
<P>
"We are stepping into the new millennium with proud. We have
enough time to develop our municipality and our country to catch
up with other developing countries," said Chea Sophara.
</P>
<P>
After the ceremony, some 2,000 people held a parade from the
bridge to Wat Phnom with holding a 2,000 metre-long "Karama" which
marks the new century and new millennium.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony is a part of the cerebration held in Phnom Penh to
usher the new millennium which will also feature fireworks, light
and sound show and dancing until dawn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
