<HEADLINE> Malaysian King's 2000 New Year Message </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Yang di-
Pertuan Agong (King) Sultan Salahuddin Friday called on the people
to resolve to cooperate with the government and help it implement
all its policies and plans to ensure that Malaysia enters the new
millennium with resounding success.
</P>
<P>
The supreme head of state also urged all civil servants to work
harder to ensure success in developing the nation.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that the new strategies to modernize the civil service
can be implemented so that it can achieve world standing in the
new millennium," he said in his 2000 New Year message released by
Istana Negara (State Palace) here.
</P>
<P>
The King said all Malaysians must be able to mould their
country's future according to their aspirations.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia must chart its own destiny and implement policies and
strategies that could put its economy on track for success for the
wealth of the nation and its people, he said.
</P>
<P>
The advent of the year 2000 brings with it challenges to the
country's development and the first day itself already poses a
challenge with the Y2K problem, he said, however he was confident
that with wisdom, effort and preparation, the country could
overcome the Y2K problem without affecting the people and the
administration of the country.
</P>
<P>
The year 2000 would spur further economic development until
2020 to realize the country's vision to achieve developed nation
status, he said, adding the country's wealth depended very much on
political and economic stability.
</P>
<P>
"Political stability will serve as a catalyst and draw new
investments from both within and outside the country. These
investments will be able to help raise Malaysia's economic
performance in the long run," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he said the reverse would happen if the people did not
think of the consequences to the economy if they always fought
over politics.
</P>
<P>
The King wished all Malaysians a Happy New Year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
