<HEADLINE> 14,000 Cops Deployed in Manila on New Year's Eve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- All the 14,000 policemen in the
Philippine capital of Manila were deployed to protect the revelers
as the New Year's eve will be marked at midnight, officials said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Franklin Bucayu, spokesman for the National Capital Regional
Police Office (NCRPO), said in a press release that all the police
districts in the capital were on red alert as the year 2000 is
being welcomed by Metro Manilans.
</P>
