President Putin as the Russian people begin this process of making
the transition from one democratically elected president to the
other," he said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the White House called Yeltsin's resignation as
dramatic, but not a complete surprise.
</P>
<P>
At the Pentagon, all questions on the impact of Yeltsin's
resignation were being referred to the White House and the State
Department. Spokeswoman Susan Hansen said U.S.-Russian military
cooperation was not expected to be affected, citing the latest
example as the U.S. and Russian teams of nuclear experts sitting
side by side in Colorado Springs Friday to ensure that the year
doesn't end with an accidental nuclear launch because of the Y2K
bug. 
