<HEADLINE> China's Central Bank to Issue Commemorative Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- China's central bank will
issue commemorative currency in the year 2000 in celebration of
the new century.
</P>
<P>
A 100-yuan bill and the 10-yuan coin will be circulated with
the existing currency of the same denominations, according to the
People's Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
The face of the gold-yellow note bears a dragon design,
representative of the coming Year of the Dragon according to the
Chinese zodiac. The flip side features the China Centenary Altar,
a structure in west Beijing, which symbolizes China's 5,000-year-
old civilization and its people's wishes for the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
Advanced anti-counterfeiting technology will be used to make
the note, according to the bank. 
