<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Party Leader Meets with Chinese FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Le Kha Phieu, general secretary
of the Communist Party of Vietnam, met with Chinese Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Tang conveyed the warm regards from General
Secretary of the Chinese Communist Party Jiang Zemin to the
Vietnamese party leader.
</P>
<P>
Tang said China and Vietnam had just experienced an important
moment in the history of their bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The Treaty of Land Border between China and Vietnam was finally
officially signed in Hanoi on Thursday after more than 20 years of
negotiations, he said, stressing that it was a delightful event in
the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The settlement of the land border issues is, first and foremost,
attributed to the vision of and effective guidance given by the
leaders of the two countries, particularly the general secretaries
of the two parties, who had pointed out the orientation and given
the motive force for the negotiations, he said.
</P>
<P>
With the signing of the treaty, the two countries will bring
peace, friendship and stability along their land border into the
21st century, which will not only benefit the two countries'
people and their coming generations, but will also be important
for promoting the relations between the two parties and two
countries and comprehensive bilateral cooperation in various
fields, as well as for peace and stability in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
The hard-won successes in the land border negotiations will
serve as a model for the two countries to resolve their remaining
issues left over from history.
</P>
<P>
Facts, he said, have once again shown to the world that China
and Vietnam are fully capable of properly resolving issues left
over from history through friendly consultations.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Vietnamese Party leader Phieu described the
signing of the Vietnam-China Land Border Treaty as of great
significance in the friendly cooperative ties between the two
countries that have been built on the basis of mutual trust.
</P>
<P>
He added that the signing of the treaty was made possible
thanks to the great efforts made by both sides and it represented
another firm step forward in promoting good-neighborliness and
friendly relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
It will make positive impacts on regional peace and stability
as well, he said.
</P>
<P>
Tang noted the very fine development of the relations between
the two parties and countries.
</P>
<P>
Regular contacts between the two countries' leaders have
enhanced mutual trust and strengthened the solidarity between
China and Vietnam, giving important guidance to the further
development of the relations between the two parties and countries,
he said.
</P>
<P>
As mankind will usher in a new millennium in a few hours, "we
cherish all the more dearly the hard-won peaceful environment and
the traditional friendship between the two parties, two countries
and two peoples," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his strong belief in the still better relations
between China and Vietnam in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Party leader Phieu said the most important thing in
the Vietnam-China relations is that the two countries' top leaders
have agreed on complete closure of the past and building of a
future of friendship and mutual trust.
</P>
<P>
He reaffirmed Vietnam's policy of developing the good-
neighborliness and friendly cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
The spirit of cooperation between Vietnam and China shown by
both sides in the land border negotiations would vigorously help
boost the development of the bilateral ties in various fields, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Drawing on the experience in the negotiations, Vietnam and
China should resolve the remaining bilateral issues left over by
history at an early date, he added.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Phieu and Tang also exchanged views on regional
and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Phieu asked the Chinese foreign minister to convey his best
wishes to General Secretary Jiang Zemin and other Chinese party
and state leaders.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Tang also met with Vietnamese State
President Tran Duc Luong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
