<HEADLINE> Chronology of Hijacking of Indian Plane (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Following is a chronology of
the eight-day long hijacking ordeal of Indian Airlines flight IC-
814. The hijacking was the longest in the country's civil aviation
history.
</P>
<P>
December 24:
</P>
<P>
- Flight IC-814 takes off from Tribhuvan International Airport
in Kathmandu at 16:25 hours
</P>
<P>
- The Airbus A-300 is hijacked at 16:55 hours while it was
flying over Lucknow
</P>
<P>
- Hijacked aircraft enters Pakistan airspace, refused
permission to land at Lahore
</P>
<P>
- Aircraft lands at Amritsar at 19:49 hours with barely 10
minutes of fuel
</P>
<P>
- Hijacked plane lands at Lahore at 20:20 hours
</P>
<P>
- Aircraft refueled at Lahore
</P>
<P>
- Aircraft takes off from Lahore at 20:37, heads for Kabul
where it is denied landing
</P>
<P>
December 25:
</P>
<P>
- Airliner allowed to land in Dubai at 01:00 hours
</P>
<P>
- Hijackers reportedly kill Rupin Katyal after he refused to
follow their dictates
</P>
<P>
- Hijackers release 27 passengers including women, children
and dead body of Rupin Katyal at 06:30
</P>
<P>
- Leaves Dubai Air Base for Southern Afghan city of Kandahar
</P>
<P>
- Lands in Kandahar at 08:33 hours
</P>
<P>
- A special aircraft to carry released passengers arrives in
Dubai, leaves and reaches a military airport at 22:15 hours
</P>
<P>
- Hijackers demand release of jailed militant leader Maulana
Masood Azhar
</P>
<P>
December 26:
</P>
<P>
- A three-member UN team led by Erick De Mul leaves for
Kandahar to provide humanitarian assistance to victims of the
hijacked aircraft
</P>
<P>
- One passenger, Anil Khurana, released by hijackers after his
health condition worsens
</P>
<P>
- UN delegation except De Mul leaves Kandahar for Islamabad
</P>
<P>
- Pakistan grants permission to India to use its airspace for
flying a special plane to Kandahar with relief and negotiating
team
</P>
<P>
- Indian External Affairs Minister hints that a team would go
to hold negotiations with the hijackers
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
