<HEADLINE> Foreign Exchange Rates in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar ended mildly
cheaper against the Indian rupee at 43.49/50 per dollar and the
British pound ended lower at 70.21/23 per pound at the close of
the interbank foreign exchange (FOREX) market in Mumbai (Bombay)
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Following are interbank FOREX rates and the rate of the Reserve
Bank of India (RBI):
</P>
<P>
Unit Interbank RBI Reference Rate
