<HEADLINE> HK's Chief Executive Sends Millennium Message (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of
China, delivered his Millennium Address to the Hong Kong people on
Friday, wishing Hong Kong continuing success and his country a
prosperous and bright future.
</P>
<P>
"We are on the threshold of a new century and a new millennium.
A deeper insight of the past will enable us to be better equipped
to take on the future and to challenge what lies ahead," said Tung.
</P>
<P>
He said: "On 1 July 1997, Hong Kong returned to China and
commenced implementation of the novel and unique concept of 'one
country, two systems.' The progress we have made in the last two
and a half years is a testimony to the ability of Hong Kong people
to withstand unprecedented difficulties and challenges. We have
maintained social stability, the rule of law and Hong Kong's
lifestyle. We have turned the concept of 'one country, two systems
' into reality."
</P>
<P>
He said that despite the Asian financial turmoil, they were
pleased to see that Hong Kong was recovering, the market was
picking up and job opportunities were increasing.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that the situation will continue to improve, "
Tung said.
</P>
<P>
A new era with remarkable and dynamic technological development
was unfolding, he noted. Technological advances would change
fundamentally the manner in which the world competes. For any
country, region or individual, the only way to maintain
competitive edge in the long run was to acquire knowledge.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
