<HEADLINE> Iran Holds Rallies to Support Palestinian Struggles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of fasting
Iranians from various walks of life on Friday poured into streets
throughout the country, voicing their support for the Palestinian
struggles and condemning any compromise with Israel.
</P>
<P>
Carrying placards with pictures of the ancient al-Aqsa mosque in
Jerusalem, pictures of Iranian leaders as well as anti-Israel and
anti-U.S. slogans, the demonstrators in the Iranian capital marched
from six predetermined routes to Tehran University, where the
Friday prayer congregations are held.
</P>
<P>
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami also took part in the rally
in front of the main gate of the Tehran University and many
demonstrators rushed to see him as his car was passing by.
</P>
<P>
In 1980, the late Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah Musavi
Khomeini announced the last Friday of the Islamic holy fasting
month of Ramadhan as the International Qods Day, calling for
international support for the Palestinians to "liberate" Jerusalem
from the Israeli occupation.
</P>
<P>
A five-point resolution was read at the end of the ally in
Tehran, condemning the Israeli regime and voicing support for the
Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
The resolution also called on the Islamic governments and the
Organization of the Islamic Conference "to pave the way by using
all the legitimate mechanisms" to support the overall campaign
against Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
