<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 31 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 Tamil rebels had
been killed in a heavy fighting between government troops and
rebels in the Northern Province of Sri Lanka Thursday, military
spokesman said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said around 5:45 a.m. Thursday Tamil rebels fired
artillery and mortars towards southern and western government
troops' defenses of the Elephant pass and attempted to breach the
defenses for more than five times. All the attempts made by the
rebels to breach the defenses were effectively repulsed by the
troops with the support of artillery and helicopter gunships of
the air force.
</P>
<P>
The troops confirmed that at least 20 rebels have been killed
and many more others have been injured during the confrontations,
the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The rebels captured a key military base near the Elephant Pass
and downed a government troops' helicopter last week, the sources
added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country since 1983. 
