<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Bangladeshi Sea Resort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake rocked southeast
Bangladesh's sea resort town of Cox's Bazar and its adjoining
areas on Friday, damaging at least 200 houses, the official BSS
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The quake hit the town and its adjoining areas including
Moheshkhali island in the Bay of Bengal at 6:50 a.m. local time
and lasted about 40 to 45 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The people of Moheshkhali, experiencing the tremor followed by
a big bang, came out of their houses in panic and took shelters in
open places.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary reports said that at least 200 houses were damaged
by the quake. This was the 5th earthquake that rocked Cox's Bazar
in six months, the BSS said.
</P>
<P>
A mild earthquake rocked the Maheshkali Island, 25 kilometers
from Cox's Bazar, in late July this year, killing five people,
injuring about 200 others and damaging thousands of houses.
</P>
