<HEADLINE> New Year's Celebrations Kick off across Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of thousands of the
New Year's Eve revelers packed every vantage point along Sydney
Harbor for Australia's biggest millennium party Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Celebrations in Sydney began on schedule at 9 p.m. with a 10-
minute fireworks displaying in cool and blustery conditions.
</P>
<P>
Barges east and west of the harbor bridge gave revelers a taste
of the massive display scheduled for the stroke of midnight.
</P>
<P>
Several areas along northern and southern shores of the harbor
were closed earlier in the evening due to overcrowding.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 6,000 boats carrying party goers crowded the
harbor.
</P>
<P>
In Canberra, the celebration began at the bank of the Lake
Burley Griffin, featuring band shows and fireworks display at 9:20
p.m.
</P>
<P>
In Melbourne, thousands of people have lined the banks of the
Yarra river to see in the New Year.
</P>
<P>
Six giant river-side screens began showing historical footage
at 6 p.m.
</P>
<P>
In the city center, hundreds of teenagers gathered at skate
park on the site of the former Queen Victoria hospital for a drug-
and alcohol-free event, Turnout Y2K.
</P>
<P>
The high point of the evening's celebrations was a fireworks
display above the city accompanied by a choreographed soundtrack.
</P>
<P>
In contrast to Sydney, Brisbane police said early crowds in the
city for the celebrations were no bigger than for a normal Friday
night.
</P>
<P>
In Perth, the New Year party mood was diminished by a bushfire
which broke out in the city's hills district during the afternoon,
destroying several homes and forcing the evacuation of 60
residents. 
</P>
