<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Civil Aviation's Flight Plans for Next 20 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, December 31 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to form a
network of air flight routes covering the entire country by 2018,
an official of the Civil Aviation Administration of China (CAAC)
said here today.
</P>
<P>
By then, China expects to have 1,618 aircraft, including 1,219
large-and medium-sized planes and 399 smaller craft.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the CAAC will schedule more
domestic flights in the next two decades for coastal, open areas,
western regions, and some central tourist destination cities.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, flight networks will continue to expand with Beijing,
Shanghai, Guangzhou and other major cities at the core, and an
increasing number of flights among provincial capitals and major
tourist cities.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, regional flights will also be further improved in
the southeastern coastal, economically-developed areas as well as
central and western regions, where transport and traffic
conditions presently are not so satisfactory.  
</P>
</TEXT>
