<HEADLINE> HK Sets up Leisure, Cultural Services Department </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 31 (Xinhua) - The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) has set up a new Leisure and
Cultural Services Department (LCSD) to provide wide ranging
leisure and cultural services to its residents and tourists
visiting Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"The main objective of LCSD's services is to promote cultural
and recreational activities, enhance arts appreciation and enrich
the quality of life," said a spokesman for the department.
</P>
<P>
The new department was formed under the Home Affairs Bureau,
and it has some 9,500 staff working in its Leisure Branch, the
Cultural Services Branch and the Administration Brach.
</P>
<P>
LCSD will be under operation on January 1st, 2000. 
</P>
