<HEADLINE> Mubarak Calls for Closer Cooperation Between Egypt, World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
has stressed the importance of enhancing Egypt's cooperation with
the other countries in the coming century when no single nation
would be able to develop on its own.
</P>
<P>
"Our relations with the world countries is strong and it will
get stronger in the future," Mubarak said on Thursday in his end-
of-the-millennium statements to the editor-in-chief of Egypt's Al-
Gomhuria daily, Samir Ragab.
</P>
<P>
"The continued development of the relations is our main concern
(as) it is impossible for any country to work alone in the future,"
the president said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mubarak affirmed that Egypt's growing ties with the
world will not overshadow its traditional and historical relations
with the Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the domestic front, the Egyptian leader underlined
the importance of adapting more to sciences and technology to help
the country face the expected fierce competition in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
The government is giving more attention to promote investments
in technology, science and information technology, "otherwise we
will lag far behind," Mubarak said, asserting that science and
technology hold the key to Egypt's progress.
</P>
<P>
"We have made so strenuous and great efforts over the past years
that we stand on solid ground and established our economy on strong
basis. It improves day after day and year after year," he added.
</P>
<P>
He voiced optimism about the future of the development in Egypt,
which he said "will be a country we all want it to be - a developed
nation" with people's living standard at high level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
