<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IDF in Lebanon Braces for More Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 31 (Xinhua)-- Israeli Defense Force (IDF) in
south Lebanon is bracing for possible more Hezbollah attacks over
the weekend, following Thursday's suicide bombing there, Israeli
security sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The bombing in a residential quarter of Klea village, less than
two kilometers from Metulla, was the first suicide attack by
Hezbollah, or Party of God, in recent years, despite recent
hummanitarian gestures by Israel to the organization.
</P>
<P>
The bombing lightly wounded an IDF solider and hurt 12 Lebanese
civilians, including children, two of them serioursly, Israel Radio
said.
</P>
<P>
The attack was aimed at disrupting the Israeli-Syrian peace
talks due to resume Monday in the United States, and the IDF has
been bracing for such attacks due to the recent setbacks the
Hebollah suffered, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the IDF is satisfied that the suicide
bombing did not succeed in dealing a serious blow to the IDF.
</P>
<P>
The suicide bombing followed a series of recent positive
developments, including the 72-hour ceasefire last week in the
security zone that enabled the Hezbollah to recover five bodies of
the Hezbollah gunmen from the field, the return of two bodies of
Hezbollah killed inside the security zone earlier this month, and
the release of five Lebanese held in administrative detentions by
Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israel Thursday night called for an urgent meeting of the Grapes
of Wrath monitoring group in Lebanon over the wounding of innocent
civilians in the bombing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
