<HEADLINE> Russian President Yeltsin Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
announced his resignation Friday and named Prime Minister Putin as
acting president.
</P>
<P>
In a television announcement, Yeltsin said: " I am going. I am
going earlier than my established time." He added that Russia
needs new political leaders to lead it into the new century.
</P>
