<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Coffee Production to Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Coffee production in
Tanzania is expected to reach 48,000 tons in the forthcoming crop
season, 5,000 tons more than the 1998-99 season, news report said
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Managing Director of the Tanzania Coffee Board Leslie Omari
attributed the increase to the positive response by coffee farmers
to abide by the basic nursing rules from the crop as well as
measures to curb smuggling, the Daily News newspaper reported.
</P>
<P>
There has been comparably increase in coffee production almost
in all coffee growing areas nationwide, Omari said, adding that by
the year 2005, the annual production will be 60,000 tons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
