<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ocalan's Retrial Appeal Rebuffed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- An appeal made by the imprisoned
leader of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK), Abdullah
Ocalan, for retrial of his death sentence, was rejected Thursday by
Vural Savas, Chief Prosecutor of Appeals Court.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan was condemned to death in June for treason and for
leading a 15-year anti-government guerrilla war, which resulted in
the deaths of 30,000 PKK members, soldiers and civilians, reported
the Anatolia News Agency on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Savas dismissed Thursday Ocalan's last-ditch appeal for a "
correction" of his sentence on the ground that there were no "legal
short falls or mistakes" warranting a "correction" of the death
sentence in the State Security Court (DGM) verdict.
</P>
<P>
"No deficiencies or omissions affecting the main ruling were
determined in the local court's verdict," he added.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was the last legal action prior to the death sentence
goes to Parliament and later to President Suleiman Demirel for
approval.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan's lawyer Ercan Kanar lodged the appeal last week, months
after an appeals court upheld Ocalan's death sentence for
treason. "We will not prepare our case for the European Court
of Human Rights," he disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The lawyers of the European Court have taken the case to the
court based in Strasbourg, France, asking Turkey not to execute
Ocalan until the court has reviewed the case, which could take up
two years.
</P>
<P>
However, Savas insisted that the government is not obliged to
abide by the European Court's ruling and can proceed with legal
procedure.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the issue has changed from a legal procedure to a
political problem under the background of Turkey's bid for a
candidacy status of the 15-member European Union, which strongly
stands against the death sentence.
</P>
<P>
It is widely held that the Turkish authorities will have to
comply in the end, now that Turkey was accepted by EU as a
candidate at its Helsinki summit earlier this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19991231.0143 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
