<HEADLINE> Manila to Strengthen Employment Programs in 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government will
strengthen its employment programs in the year 2000 and onwards,
Bienvenido Laguesma, secretary of the Department of Labor and
Employment (DOLE), said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Laguesma said in a report that important strides were made by
DOLE in 1999, especially in facilitating and enhancing employment,
which are crucial to economic recovery and progress.
</P>
<P>
He added an effort to firm up these gains and strengthen the
linkages with key sectors will be made next year in the fight
against poverty and joblessness, and also to enhance the country's
attractiveness to investments and jobs.
</P>
<P>
Laguesma said assistance to some 53,038 workers displaced by
the Asian financial crisis were extended by appropriate DOLE
offices in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Among those extended assistance, he said, were industrial
workers, workers of small and medium enterprises, rural workers
and laborers. 
</P>
