<DOCNO> XIE19991231.0144 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jakarta Bourse Makes Good Performance in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Jakarta
Stock Exchange (JSX) ended the year of 1999 with a 70 percent
gain, leaving the bourse as one of best in performing markets in
the world.
</P>
<P>
Based on data issued by the Capital Supervisory Board (BAPEPAM),
the JSX ranked the third among the world's best performing markets
in 1999 after South Korea's Seoul and Singapore Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The composite index on the bourse increased 70.06 percent
during 1999 and closed at 676.91 points on Thursday, the last
trading day in the year.
</P>
<P>
"The year of 1999 is the recovery year for the Indonesian
capital market," the Jakarta Post daily quoted the Bapepam
research bureau as saying on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The JSX composite index jumped to its highest point at 716.46
in mid-June and dipped to the lowest level at 327.31 in mid-March.
The composite index closed last year trading at 398.03 points,"
the daily quoted a report issued by the bureau as saying.
</P>
<P>
It also said that trade and service companies performed the
best on the JSX, booking a 241.82 percent gain during 1999.
</P>
<P>
But agriculture sector companies were reportedly sluggish,
booking a loss of 23.71 percent during the year.
</P>
<P>
The report also said that the value of daily trading on the
bourse stood at average of 594.2 billion rupiah (84.8 million U.S.
dollars) for the year, compared to 403.6 billion rupiah (57.5
million U.S. dollars) a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Market capitalization jumped to 443.3 trillion rupiah (63.3
billion dollars) in the year from 175.7 trillion rupiah in 1998 (
25 billion dollars), the report said.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the bourse performance, Chairman of Bapepam Jusuf
Anwar said,"this (the best performance) shows that confidence in (
the country's) capital market had been recover." "But there will
be a tough challenge in the future. We have to keep working hard,"
Anwar was quoted by the Bisnis Indonesia as saying.
</P>
<P>
The trading activities on the bourse will be closed on Friday
and Monday and resume on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
