<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hke123121-- Thailand Claims Y2K Readiness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai and Deputy Prime Minister
Trairong Suwannakhiri, who is in charge of overseeing the national
Y2K problem, affirmed on Friday that Thailand is well-prepared to
welcome the new millennium, TNA said.
</P>
<P>
Chuan suggested the public not to panic or over-fear of the so-
called millennium bug, saying Thailand could learn about any
problem in advance from countries which enter the new year hours
before Thailand, TNA said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the National Electronic and Computer Technology
Center (NECTEC) has confirmed that all the agencies in Thailand,
which seriously need Y2K compliance, are now 100 percent ready.
</P>
<P>
The Defense Ministry assured that it had been well-prepared to
prevent any Y2K problem related to armed weapon and thus the
millennium bug would not have any impact on national security.
</P>
<P>
The Public Health Ministry also assured that hospitals had been
well-equipped with medical, energy and other necessary facilities
to provide normal services to patients.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Airways International, Thailand's national carrier,
announced that it had successfully overcome the Y2K computer
glitch, though it canceled and rescheduled some international
flights based on its pre-cautious policy.
</P>
<P>
The airline also established a Y2K command center to monitor
the situation at the turn of the century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
