<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pistons Beat Hawks on Mills' 3-pointer in Overtime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Terry Mills' 3-pointer at
the end of overtime brought the Detroit Pistons a 106-105 triumph
over the Hawks in Auburn Hills, Michigan on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Jimmy Jackson scored 26 points for the Hawks, who appeared to
have taken control with an 8-0 run in overtime.
</P>
<P>
Alan Henderson made two free throws with 10 seconds to time
that gave Atlanta a 105-103 lead.
</P>
<P>
The Pistons called timeout with five seconds remaining and
Grant Hill took the ensuing inbounds pass and sent a pass to Mills,
who calmly scored his 30th 3-pointer of the season as the buzzer
sounded.
</P>
<P>
In Dallas, Tracy McGrady scored 24 points to lead the Toronto
Raptors to a 109-104 victory over the Dallas Mavericks. He hit 10-
of-16 shots from the field and added 11 rebounds, which brought
the Raptors to a third straight road game win for the first time
this season.
</P>
<P>
Vince Carter scored 22 points, grabbed eight rebounds and
dished eight assists for the Raptors.
</P>
<P>
In Denver, Paul Pierce scored 21 points when the Boston Celtics
enjoyed a 102-94 victory over the Denver Nuggets.
</P>
<P>
Antoine Walker scored 26 points for Boston.
</P>
<P>
In Houston, Kelvin Cato had 21 points and 11 rebounds as the
Houston Rockets beat the Los Angeles Clippers 122-100.
</P>
<P>
In Indianapolis, Reggie Miller scored 30 points as the Indiana
Pacers reached their fifth straight victory, 109-99 over the
Charlotte Hornets.
</P>
<P>
In Milwaukee, the Bucks escaped with a 91-90 victory over the
Cleveland Cavaliers.
</P>
<P>
In East Rutherford, New Jersey, Stephon Marbury had 21 points
and 13 assists as the New Jersey Nets downed the Orlando Magic 102-
92.
</P>
<P>
Jamie Feick scored 16 points and had 15 rebounds for the Nets.
</P>
<P>
In Vancouver, Tim Duncan scored 32 points and grabbed 15
rebounds as the San Antonio Spurs notched their ninth straight win
against the Vancouver Grizzlies and third in five games with a 98-
88 triumph.
</P>
<P>
In Washington, Patrick Ewing scored 13 points as the New York
Knicks edged the Wizards 89-86.
</P>
<P>
In Minneapolis, The Chicago Bulls, after reaching glorious
heights in the decade with six NBA titles, ended the 1990s with a
humiliating defeat, a 94-76 loss to the Minnesota Timberwolves.
</P>
<P>
In Portland, Rasheed Wallace had 23 points and 11 rebounds as
the Portland Trail Blazers post a 108-90 victory over a streaky
Philadelphia 76ers to close out the century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
