<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SW China Province Launches Development Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The government of southwest
China's Sichuan Province has launched 38 key development projects
involving a total investment of 250 billion yuan (about 30 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
These projects encompass a variety of fields ranging from
agriculture, infrastructure, and power to the raw materials
industry, tourism, high-technology, and environmental protection,
said a local government official.
</P>
<P>
They especially feature the further development of western
Sichuan, said the official, adding that this area is rich in
natural resources and has considerable potential for investment
and development.
</P>
<P>
The province will carry out a series of favorable policies to
attract investors worldwide, he added. 
</P>
