<HEADLINE> Thousands Tie Knot in Thailand for New Millennium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 31 (Xinhua) -- About 2,000 couples attended a
Year 2000 mass wedding ceremony Friday morning on the outskirts of
Bangkok, which will last until the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony began at 09:30 a.m. (0230 GMT) with the unveiling
of a 2.5-meter-high golden Sculpture of Love 2000, with the names
of the couples engraved on it.
</P>
<P>
The event will be followed by a traditional Thai engagement
ceremony, offering food to Buddhist monks, a traditional nuptial
water ceremony, the wedding itself and a New-Year countdown.
</P>
<P>
The wedding, a millennium tourism promotion called Thailand
Amazing Love 2000, has been one of Thailand's most publicized
celebrations on the New Year's Eve.
</P>
<P>
The wedding mainly involves Thais after a large number of
foreigners decided against taking flights here because of Y2K
jitters.
</P>
<P>
Originally, the 2,000 couples are supposed to be consisted of
1,700 from Thailand and 300 from the United Stated, Cambodia,
China, France, Germany, Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, Sweden,
Ukraine and elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
But the organizer said they have prepared a long reserve list
of Thai couples to replace the withdrawn foreign couples, so they
are sure there are 2,000 couples present.
</P>
<P>
A 72-tier, 9.9-meter-high wedding cake has been prepared for
the couples, who will be given an opportunity to pose with it.
</P>
<P>
Many couples said they were keen to take part in such a large
event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
