team bus.
</P>
<P>
Gugliotta may play in the Suns'next game, at home next Tuesday
night against the Charlotte Hornets.
</P>
<P>
While hospitalized, Gugliotta underwent on a cellular phone
with his wife after a 110-102 victory at Portland on December 17.
He has missed the last seven games.
</P>
<P>
Gugliotta and the Suns were fortunate the seizure occurred on
the team bus, which was headed to the airport. Once on the return
flight to Phoenix, he may not have able to receive proper medical
attention.
</P>
<P>
Gugliotta, who turned 30 two days after suffering the seizure,
is in his second season with the Suns, his fourth NBA team. He is
averaging 14.1 points and 8.1 rebounds in 22 games this season.
</P>
<P>
A 1997 All-Star with the Minnesota Timberwolves, Gugliotta
signed as a free agent with Phoenix prior to last season. 
