</P>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA -- Organization of American States (OAS) mediator
Luigi Einaudi announced that Nicaragua and Honduras agreed
Thursday on an immediate separation of their military forces in
the border to prevent more incidents.
</P>
<P>
The OAS official also said in a report received here from Miami,
United States, that the two countries agreed to define a zone of
exclusion in the Caribbean area.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Nicaragua and Honduras have soured after the
Honduran congress ratified a treaty of maritime limits on November
30 with Colombia, which Managua alleges that it takes off 130,000
square kilometers of Atlantic waters rich in fishing and potential
oil and natural gas resources. (Nicaragua-Honduras-Agreement)
