Cuba to demand the return to the island of Cuban boy Elian
Gonzalez, who survived a wreckage last month and is now in the
United States.
</P>
<P>
"Open forums" have been organized at which the "kidnapping" of
Elian by "Yankee imperialism" and "the counter-revolutionary mafia
of Miami" are denounced.
</P>
<P>
Elian Gonzalez was rescued in the sea where he was holding to
an inflated inner tube after surviving the sinking of a raft in
which some Cubans pretended to reach the United States soil. Elian
's mother and other 11 people drowned.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban government has insisted that Elian must return to his
father, who is in the island. (Cuba-March-Boy)
