the hotel and seized two weapons.
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- The new Venezuelan Constitution approved in the
December 15 referendum went into force Thursday after its
publication.
</P>
<P>
Some of the main innovations in the new constitution text,
formed by nine chapters and 350 articles, are the change of the
name of Republica de Venezuela to Bolivarian Republic of Venezuela,
the Congress restructuring, which now is named National Assembly,
the creation of two new public powers, and the figure of vice-
president or prime minister
</P>
<P>
The military right to vote and the extension of the
presidential mandate to six years, instead of five, with the
possibility of an immediate reelection, are also among the
innovations. (Venezuela-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- The U.S. national flag was hauled down Thursday
afternoon in the Panama Canal Zone, at the request of the U.S.
government.
</P>
<P>
This U.S. flag is the last one pulled down before December 31,
when the government of the United States will handover the
interoceanic waterway and its installations to the Panamanian
sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
According to the schedule of events for the Canal handover,
this U.S. bars and starts flag must be lowered at 12:00 (local
time) of Friday, December 31, as stipulated in the Torrijos-Carter
treaties, signed by Panama and the United States in 1977.
</P>
<P>
Simultaneously the Panamanian national flag will be hoisted. (
US-Panama) 
</P>
