<HEADLINE> Spain Writes off Honduran Debt of 20 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, December 30 (Xinhua) -- The Spanish government Thursday
decided to forgive 20 million U.S. dollars in Honduras' debt
service.
</P>
<P>
This move aims to help a rapid recovery of the Central American
country from the disaster caused by hurricane Mitch in October
1998, said officials.
</P>
<P>
The hurricane killed 9,000 people, left 2 million homeless, and
caused damage estimated at 10 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The condoned debt service is related to two loans granted to
Honduras in December 1992 and July 1996 to fund the hydroelectric
plant of Nacaome. 
</P>
