<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Argentina, No Casualties Reported </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 30 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.
5 on the Richter scale hit Argentina's northern provinces of Jujuy
and Salta on Thursday, but no casualties or damage were reported.
</P>
<P>
The National Seismic Prevention Institute said the tremor
occurred at midday, with the epicenter near Tilcara in Jujuy
Province.
</P>
<P>
The intensity of the movement was four to five degrees on the
Modified Mercalli scale in the city of San Salvador of Jujuy and
four degrees in Salta, while the Richter scale registered a
magnitude of 5.5.
</P>
<P>
The Salta Civil Defense Office reported there were no request
for assistance for injuries nor cracks in the buildings examined.
</P>
