<HEADLINE> Millions of Germans Greet New Millennium in Massive Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Over 2 million Germans gathered
around the Brandendurg Gate here, celebrating the new millennium
with cheering music and deafening fireworks.
</P>
<P>
The massive party, stretching from the middle of west Berlin
until the center of east Berlin, was the biggest in German history.
</P>
<P>
Great monuments near the open-air party, such as the
Brandenburg Gate and the Reichstag building, were illuminated
with colorful laser lights while fireworks exploding above lit up
the sky in a dizzying array of colors.
</P>
<P>
 Loud disco music echoed over the 4.5 kilometer long festival
street, where people cheered, sang and danced under sub-freezing
temperature.
</P>
<P>
 Beginning at 19.00, December 31, the festival was overcrowded
in 2 hours so that the police tightened the security checks and
prohibited newcomers to take part.
</P>
<P>
The gigantic festival, costing more than 40 million marks,
included 10 stages, 60 bands, five huge video screens and two
massive ferris wheels.
</P>
<P>
Organizers prepared more than 300,000 bottles of champagne,
two million litters of beer and a million sausages for
consumption to meet the demands of the revellers. 
</P>
